The paper deals with the integration of deep learning and logical reasoning for visual question answering, which is a problem in computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of decision tree induction and incremental learning, which are topics in machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates the architecture in the context of a simulated robot, indicating a potential connection to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) a possible sub-category.
